Consider the diagram
\usepackage {amsmath} \usepackage {amssymb} \usepackage {tikz-cd} \begin {tikzcd}[row sep=huge] & 0 \ar [d] & 0 \ar [d] \\0 \ar [r] & W_{-1}(T_\mathbb {C}(M))\cap F^0 \ar [r] \ar [d] & F^0 \ar [r] \ar [d] & V \ar [r] \ar [d,"\sim "] & 0 \\0 \ar [r] & \operatorname {H}_1(G,\mathbb {Z})\otimes \mathbb {C} \ar [r] \ar [d] & T_\mathbb {Z}(M)\otimes \mathbb {C} \ar [r] \ar [d] & X\otimes \mathbb {C} & 0 \\ & \operatorname {Lie}(G) \ar [r,equals] \ar [d] & \operatorname {Lie}(G) \ar [d] \\ & 0 & 0 \end {tikzcd}
Since F^0 is sent to \operatorname {Gr}_0^W(T_\mathbb {C}(M)), it is thus of type (0,0).

