Let S=P^t (the topological space consisting of a single point). We see that, for a sheaf F^\bullet on X_\bullet , the \Gamma (X_n,F^n) are the components of a cosimplicial set \Gamma ^\bullet (X_\bullet ,F^\bullet ). The functor \Gamma (of global sections) is the functor
